This article is a statement from the President following a conversation he had with Vice President Biden, Professor Gates, and Sergeant Crowley. The President expressed his gratitude to both Professor Gates and Sergeant Crowley for joining him in a friendly and thoughtful conversation at the White House. He mentioned that before they sat down for a beer, the two gentlemen spent some time listening to each other, which he commended. The President emphasized his belief that what unites us is stronger than what divides us and expressed confidence that this conversation had brought them closer together. He expressed hope that everyone could learn a positive lesson from this episode.